        "subject": "LU-20178 osc: wire protocol and UAPI definitions for CSDC",
        "message": "LU-20178 osc: wire protocol and UAPI definitions for CSDC\n\nAdd wire protocol structures and UAPI definitions for client-side\ndata compression (CSDC). This includes:\n\n- New compression type and chunk size fields in struct\n  lov_comp_md_entry_v1 for per-component compression settings\n- OBD_CONNECT2_COMPRESS connect flag for client/server\n  negotiation of compression capability\n- UAPI header lustre_compr.h defining supported compression\n  algorithms (lz4, lz4hc, lzo), compression levels, and\n  chunk sizes (64KB to 4MB)\n- Wire protocol test updates in wirecheck.c and wiretest.c\n  to validate the new fields\n\nSigned-off-by: Brian Barbisch <brbarbis@microsoft.com>\nTest-Parameters: Ignore\nChange-Id: I3791552a09870c7e77eefaf57e8fd5954d230338\n"
      },
      "branch": "refs/heads/master"
    }
  },
